CATCHHIMANDFREEHIM chased between rivals, then three wide on the turn and weakened. COMMISSION ALWAYS chased three wide, then four wide on the turn and gave way.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOLDEN HEART stalked two wide, steadied in tight between rivals at the four and a half furlong marker, moved up inside on the far turn, rallied on the rail, closed willingly and moved to a clear lead, then held on late. COMPASS FIRE set the pace on the inside, showed the way past the quarter pole, drifted out bothering rivals at the eighth pole, then weakened. NOW YUS CANT LEAVE raced three wide early, stalked three wide, chased two wide on the far turn, rallied between rivals, steadied at the eighth pole and finished evenly. FABULOUS CANDY steadied at the start, raced off the rail, off the pace and gave way on the far turn. After a Stewards' Inquiry and Jockey Objection by the rider of NOW YUS CANT LEAVE against the fourth place finisher, COMPASS FIRE was disqualifed and placed fifth.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MY BOY COLTON tracked on the inside, saved ground on the far turn, moved up on the rail, angled out at the eighth pole, rallied between rivals, was bumped at the sixteenth marker and finished willingly for the win. THE MAN TO SEE raced off the pace inside, steadied entering the first turn, advanced on the far turn, rallied three wide into the stretch, closed outside rivals, was bumped at the sixteenth pole and then closed for second. SPANISH CZAR set the pace on the inside, showed the way on the far turn, dug in gamely on the rail in the stretch drive, drifted out bumping rivals at the sixteenth marker and was outfinished. TIZ TACT TOE stalked two wide, chased on the far turn, rallied between rivals into the stretch, steadied in tight at the sixteenth marker and was outkicked. LAST SECOND LOUIE broke outward, raced three wide on the first turn, settled two wide off the pace, saved ground on the far turn, rallied mildly and then flattened out. AIRMAN was outrun early, advanced inside on the far turn and failed to threaten. OUT OF TOWNER raced three wide off the pace, chased on the turn, came four wide into the lane and weakened. GOLDEN CHELLA was off slowly, raced off the rail, off the pace and did not factor. COUNTRY CHARLIE stalked the pace, chased three wide on the far turn and tired. TUCKER ROAD raced four wide on the first turn, stalked outside and gave way on the far turn. RUSHIN TOTHECIRCLE was outrun. LYING JEFF raced off the pace inside, was pulled up on the far turn and walked off. After a Stewards' Inquiry into the stretch run, the race was declared official.
